#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:1
msgid "VTK XML Reader/Writer Information Format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:3
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:5
msgid ""
"The vtk xml data file readers / writers store certain `vtkInformation` "
"entries that are set on `vtkAbstractArray`'s `GetInformation()` object. "
"Support is currently limited to numeric and string information keys, both "
"single- and vector-valued. Only the information objects attached to arrays "
"are written/read."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:10
msgid "Array Information"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:12
msgid ""
"Array information is embedded in the `<DataArray>` XML element as a series "
"of `<InformationKey>` elements. The required attributes `name` and "
"`location` specify the name and location strings associated with the key -- "
"for instance, the `vtkDataArray::UNITS_LABEL()` key has "
"`name=\"UNITS_LABEL\"` and `location=\"vtkDataArray\"`. The `length` "
"attribute is required for vector keys."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:18
msgid ""
"<DataArray [...]>\n"
"  <InformationKey name=\"KeyName\" "
"location=\"KeyLocation\" [ length=\"N\" ]>\n"
"    [...]\n"
"  </InformationKey>\n"
"  <InformationKey [...]>\n"
"    [...]\n"
"  </InformationKey>\n"
"  [...]\n"
"</DataArray>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:31
msgid "Specific examples of supported key types:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:33
msgid "vtkInformationDoubleKey"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../design_documents/IOXMLInformationFormat.md:35
msgid ""
